definitions.Checksum.description: The expected state of a client's local database.
definitions.Checksum.properties.sha256.d:
The SHA256 hash of the client state; that is, of the sorted list of all
hashes present in the database.
definitions.ClientInfo.description: The client metadata associated with Safe Browsing API requests.
definitions.ClientInfo.properties.client:
A client ID that (hopefully) uniquely identifies the client implementation
of the Safe Browsing API.
The version of the client implementation.
definitions.Constraints.properties.maxDa:
Sets the maximum number of entries that the client is willing to have
in the local database. This should be a power of 2 between 2**10 and
2**20. If zero, no database size limit is set.
definitions.Constraints.properties.maxUp:
The maximum size in number of entries. The update will not contain more
entries than this value.  This should be a power of 2 between 2**10 and
2**20.  If zero, no update size limit is set.
definitions.Constraints.properties.regio:
Requests the list for a specific geographic location. If not set the
server may pick that value based on the user's IP address. Expects ISO
3166-1 alpha-2 format.
definitions.Constraints.properties.suppo: The compression types supported by the client.
definitions.FetchThreatListUpdatesReques:
Describes a Safe Browsing API update request. Clients can request updates for
multiple lists in a single request.
NOTE: Field index 2 is unused.
NEXT: 5
definitions.FetchThreatListUpdatesRespon: The list updates requested by the clients.

The minimum duration the client must wait before issuing any update
request. If this field is not set clients may update as soon as they want.
definitions.FindFullHashesRequest.descri: Request to return full hashes matched by the provided hash prefixes.
definitions.FindFullHashesRequest.proper:
Client metadata associated with callers of higher-level APIs built on top
of the client's implementation.
The current client states for each of the client's local threat lists.
The lists and hashes to be checked.
definitions.FindFullHashesResponse.prope: The full hashes that matched the requested prefixes.

The minimum duration the client must wait before issuing any find hashes
request. If this field is not set, clients can issue a request as soon as
they want.

For requested entities that did not match the threat list, how long to
cache the response.
definitions.FindThreatMatchesRequest.des: Request to check entries against lists.
definitions.FindThreatMatchesRequest.pro: The lists and entries to be checked for matches.
definitions.ListThreatListsResponse.prop: The lists available for download by the client.
definitions.ListUpdateRequest.properties: The constraints associated with this request.
The type of platform at risk by entries present in the list.

The current state of the client for the requested list (the encrypted
client state that was received from the last successful list update).
The types of entries present in the list.
The type of threat posed by entries present in the list.
definitions.ListUpdateResponse.descripti: An update to an individual list.
definitions.ListUpdateResponse.propertie:
A set of entries to add to a local threat type's list. Repeated to allow
for a combination of compressed and raw data to be sent in a single
response.

The expected SHA256 hash of the client state; that is, of the sorted list
of all hashes present in the database after applying the provided update.
If the client state doesn't match the expected state, the client must
disregard this update and retry later.
The new client state, in encrypted format. Opaque to clients.
The platform type for which data is returned.

A set of entries to remove from a local threat type's list. In practice,
this field is empty or contains exactly one ThreatEntrySet.

The type of response. This may indicate that an action is required by the
client when the response is received.
The threat type for which data is returned.
definitions.MetadataEntry.properties.key: The metadata entry key. For JSON requests, the key is base64-encoded.
definitions.MetadataEntry.properties.val: The metadata entry value. For JSON requests, the value is base64-encoded.
definitions.RawHashes.description:
The uncompressed threat entries in hash format of a particular prefix length.
Hashes can be anywhere from 4 to 32 bytes in size. A large majority are 4
bytes, but some hashes are lengthened if they collide with the hash of a
popular URL.

Used for sending ThreatEntrySet to clients that do not support compression,
or when sending non-4-byte hashes to clients that do support compression.
definitions.RawHashes.properties.prefixS:
The number of bytes for each prefix encoded below.  This field can be
anywhere from 4 (shortest prefix) to 32 (full SHA256 hash).
definitions.RawHashes.properties.rawHash:
The hashes, in binary format, concatenated into one long string. Hashes are
sorted in lexicographic order. For JSON API users, hashes are
base64-encoded.
definitions.RawIndices.description: A set of raw indices to remove from a local list.
definitions.RawIndices.properties.indice: The indices to remove from a lexicographically-sorted local list.
definitions.RiceDeltaEncoding.descriptio:
The Rice-Golomb encoded data. Used for sending compressed 4-byte hashes or
compressed removal indices.
definitions.RiceDeltaEncoding.properties: The encoded deltas that are encoded using the Golomb-Rice coder.

The offset of the first entry in the encoded data, or, if only a single
integer was encoded, that single integer's value.

The number of entries that are delta encoded in the encoded data. If only a
single integer was encoded, this will be zero and the single value will be
stored in `first_value`.

The Golomb-Rice parameter, which is a number between 2 and 28. This field
is missing (that is, zero) if `num_entries` is zero.
definitions.ThreatEntry.description:
An individual threat; for example, a malicious URL or its hash
representation. Only one of these fields should be set.
definitions.ThreatEntry.properties.diges:
The digest of an executable in SHA256 format. The API supports both
binary and hex digests. For JSON requests, digests are base64-encoded.
A hash prefix, consisting of the most significant 4-32 bytes of a SHA256
hash. This field is in binary format. For JSON requests, hashes are
base64-encoded.
definitions.ThreatEntryMetadata.descript:
The metadata associated with a specific threat entry. The client is expected
to know the metadata key/value pairs associated with each threat type.
definitions.ThreatEntrySet.description:
A set of threats that should be added or removed from a client's local
database.
definitions.ThreatEntrySet.properties.co: The compression type for the entries in this set.
definitions.ThreatEntrySet.properties.ra: The raw removal indices for a local list.
definitions.ThreatEntrySet.properties.ri:
The encoded 4-byte prefixes of SHA256-formatted entries, using a
Golomb-Rice encoding. The hashes are converted to uint32, sorted in
ascending order, then delta encoded and stored as encoded_data.

The encoded local, lexicographically-sorted list indices, using a
Golomb-Rice encoding. Used for sending compressed removal indices. The
removal indices (uint32) are sorted in ascending order, then delta encoded
and stored as encoded_data.
definitions.ThreatInfo.description:
The information regarding one or more threats that a client submits when
checking for matches in threat lists.
definitions.ThreatInfo.properties.platfo: The platform types to be checked.
definitions.ThreatInfo.properties.threat: The threat entries to be checked.
The entry types to be checked.
The threat types to be checked.
definitions.ThreatListDescriptor.descrip:
Describes an individual threat list. A list is defined by three parameters:
the type of threat posed, the type of platform targeted by the threat, and
the type of entries in the list.
definitions.ThreatListDescriptor.propert: The platform type targeted by the list's entries.
The entry types contained in the list.
The threat type posed by the list's entries.
definitions.ThreatMatch.description: A match when checking a threat entry in the Safe Browsing threat lists.
definitions.ThreatMatch.properties.cache:
The cache lifetime for the returned match. Clients must not cache this
response for more than this duration to avoid false positives.
definitions.ThreatMatch.properties.platf: The platform type matching this threat.
definitions.ThreatMatch.properties.threa: Optional metadata associated with this threat.
The threat entry type matching this threat.
The threat type matching this threat.
